---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { getCollection } from "astro:content";

const providers = await getCollection("providers");
const tiered = providers
  .filter((p) => p.data.partner_tier)
  .sort((a, b) => a.data.name.localeCompare(b.data.name));

const tiers = [
  {
    name: "Gold",
    target: "$6,900/mo",
    description:
      "Highest active tier with significant Frappe Cloud revenue, multiple certified professionals, and proven delivery quality. Unlocks lead sharing, deal closure assistance, and pre-sales support.",
  },
  {
    name: "Silver",
    target: "$2,875/mo",
    description:
      "Established partners with consistent Frappe Cloud sales, certified team members, and successful quality audits.",
  },
  {
    name: "Bronze",
    target: "$690/mo",
    description:
      "Active partners meeting baseline Frappe Cloud sales targets with certified professionals on their team. Listed in the official Frappe partner directory.",
  },
  {
    name: "Emerging",
    target: "$350/mo",
    description:
      "Verified by Frappe, active in projects, and steadily expanding their expertise. Building toward a full partner listing.",
  },
  {
    name: "Entry",
    target: "None",
    description:
      "Starting tier for new partners. Must upgrade at least once within one year. Frappe provides product training and certifications for two team members.",
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Frappe Partnership Levels Explained"
  description="How the Frappe partner program works: tiers, requirements, and what they mean for ERPNext service providers."
>
  <nav class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
    <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL} class="hover:text-primary">Home</a>
    <span class="mx-1">/</span>
    <span>Partnership Levels</span>
  </nav>

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary mb-3">
    Frappe Partnership Levels
  </h1>
  <p class="text-text-muted text-lg mb-8 max-w-3xl">
    Understanding what the partner tiers mean and how they are earned.
  </p>

  <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-8">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How the program works</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The Frappe partner program is <strong>primarily sales-driven</strong>.
        Partner tiers are determined by how much
        <a
          href="https://frappecloud.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-primary hover:underline">Frappe Cloud</a
        >
        managed hosting a service provider sells. The more hosting revenue a partner
        generates, the higher their tier.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This also explains why strong implementation partners can still appear in
        lower tiers. Frappe Cloud hosting is relatively inexpensive, and a plan of
        around $25 per month is common, while implementing that same site may take
        several weeks and cost more than EUR 15,000. Because the partner program
        measures recurring hosting revenue rather than implementation revenue, a
        provider can deliver substantial projects and still stay in a lower tier
        unless they manage a large number of hosted sites.
      </p>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Beyond sales volume, Frappe applies <strong>quality controls</strong>:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 pl-6 list-disc text-text">
        <li>
          <strong>Certified professionals</strong> &mdash; All partners must have
          at least two full-time team members certified through <a
            href="https://frappe.school"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-primary hover:underline">Frappe School</a
          >
          (ERPNext Functional Consultant or Frappe Framework Developer credentials).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Implementation track record</strong> &mdash; Partners need at least
          three verifiable successful ERP/ERPNext deployments to qualify.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Quality audits</strong> &mdash; Frappe conducts quarterly review
          meetings and partner audits (SOP audits), inspired by ISO 9001 process maturity
          standards. These assess implementation quality, customer satisfaction, and
          adherence to best practices.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Active cloud presence</strong> &mdash; Partners must maintain an
          active Frappe Cloud account with at least one live site.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Tier advancement and demotion</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Partners advance by meeting the sales targets of the next level for <strong
          >two consecutive quarters</strong
        >. Conversely, failing to meet targets for two consecutive quarters
        results in demotion. Entry-level partners must upgrade at least once
        within their first year.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The tiers</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {
          tiers.map((tier) => {
            const providersInTier = tiered.filter(
              (p) => p.data.partner_tier === tier.name,
            );
            return (
              <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
                <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-2">
                  <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-sm font-medium rounded-full bg-accent/10 text-accent">
                    {tier.name}{" "}
                    {tier.name !== "Emerging" && tier.name !== "Entry"
                      ? "Partner"
                      : ""}
                  </span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-text-muted">
                    Target: {tier.target}
                  </span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-3">{tier.description}</p>
                {providersInTier.length > 0 ? (
                  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-4 gap-y-1">
                    {providersInTier.map((p) => (
                      <a
                        href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/${p.data.country_slug}/${p.id}/`}
                        class="text-sm text-primary hover:underline"
                      >
                        {p.data.name}
                      </a>
                    ))}
                  </div>
                ) : (
                  <p class="text-sm text-text-muted italic">
                    No providers in this tier in our European directory yet.
                  </p>
                )}
              </div>
            );
          })
        }
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What about unlisted providers?</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Many excellent ERPNext service providers in this directory do not hold
        an official Frappe partner tier. This does not reflect on their quality
        or capability. Common reasons include:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 pl-6 list-disc text-text">
        <li>
          They offer self-hosted or third-party hosting instead of Frappe Cloud
        </li>
        <li>They are newer to the ecosystem and building their practice</li>
        <li>
          They focus on a local market where Frappe Cloud adoption is still
          growing
        </li>
        <li>They choose not to participate in the formal partner program</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="leading-relaxed mt-4">
        The partnership tier is one data point among many. When choosing a
        provider, also consider their industry expertise, local regulatory
        knowledge, language coverage, and track record.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-border pt-6">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">
        Based on information from the
        <a
          href="https://frappe.io/partners/plans"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-primary hover:underline">Frappe Partner Plans</a
        >
        and
        <a
          href="https://frappe.io/partners/faq"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-primary hover:underline">Partner FAQ</a
        >. For questions, contact <a
          href="mailto:partner@frappe.io"
          class="text-primary hover:underline">partner@frappe.io</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
